    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bevor components constituting the upper portion, covering the face from eye level to the chin where it overlapped the lower bevor; they often had small slots and holes for ventilation.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000039541/Tarassuk and Blair, Complete Encyclopedia of Arms and Armor (1979)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Componentes de la mentonera superior cubriendo la cara desde nivel del ojo a la barbilla donde se traslapa tenían a menudo ranuras y agujeros pequeños para la ventilación.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De bovenste delen van gezichtsplaten die het gezicht bedekken van ooghoogte tot  kin, waar ze de kinplaat overlappen. Ze hadden vaak kleine sleufjes en gaatjes voor ventilatie.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052462/Puype, Legermuseum Delft</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>位在上半部分的護頸甲組件，臉被遮住的部份，從視平線以下至下頦與下半護頸甲重疊的部份。通常具有通風的槽隙與小洞。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
